## Welcome! Want to learn more? See two factoextra-related books at https://goo.gl/ve3WBa
# Función para remover outliers usando IQR
remove_outliers <- function(x) {
  qnt <- quantile(x, probs=c(.25, .75), na.rm=TRUE)
  H <- 1.5 * IQR(x, na.rm=TRUE)
  x[x < (qnt[1] - H)] <- NA
  x[x > (qnt[2] + H)] <- NA
  return(x)
}

movies_clean <- movies %>%
  select(popularity, budget, revenue, runtime, 
         genresAmount, productionCoAmount, 
         productionCountriesAmount, voteCount, 
         voteAvg, actorsAmount, 
         castWomenAmount, castMenAmount) %>%
  mutate(across(everything(), as.numeric)) %>%
  # Remover outliers
  mutate(across(everything(), remove_outliers)) %>%
  # Eliminar filas con NA
  na.omit()
## Warning: There were 2 warnings in `mutate()`.
## The first warning was:
## ℹ In argument: `across(everything(), as.numeric)`.
## Caused by warning:
## ! NAs introduced by coercion
## ℹ Run `dplyr::last_dplyr_warnings()` to see the 1 remaining warning.
movies_scaled <- scale(movies_clean)

set.seed(531) # Seed para reproducibilidad
wss <- numeric(12)  
for (k in 1:12) {
  km <- kmeans(movies_scaled, 
               centers = k, 
               nstart = 50,  
               iter.max = 50)  
  wss[k] <- km$tot.withinss
}
## Warning: Quick-TRANSfer stage steps exceeded maximum (= 274850)
p <- fviz_nbclust(movies_scaled, 
             kmeans, 
             method = "wss",
             k.max = 12,  
             nstart = 50,  
             iter.max = 50) +  
  labs(title = "Método del Codo para Determinar k Óptimo",
       x = "Número de Clusters (k)",
       y = "Suma total de cuadrados dentro de clusters") +
  theme_minimal()
## Warning: Quick-TRANSfer stage steps exceeded maximum (= 274850)
print(p)

wss_diff <- diff(wss) / wss[-length(wss)] * 100
print("\nReducción porcentual en WSS para cada k adicional:")
## [1] "\nReducción porcentual en WSS para cada k adicional:"
for(i in 1:length(wss_diff)) {
  cat(sprintf("De %d a %d clusters: %.2f%% de reducción\n", 
              i, i+1, abs(wss_diff[i])))
}

Agrupamiento

# Cargar librerías necesarias
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(clustertend) # Para análisis de tendencia al agrupamiento
## Package `clustertend` is deprecated.  Use package `hopkins` instead.
library(factoextra)  # Para visualización de distancias

# 1. Cargar dataset limpio
movies_cleaned <- movies %>%
  filter(!is.na(originalLanguage) & originalLanguage != "",
         !is.na(productionCountry) & productionCountry != "",
         !is.na(budget) & budget > 0,
         !is.na(revenue) & revenue > 0,
         !is.na(runtime) & runtime > 0) %>%
  select(budget, revenue, runtime, voteAvg, voteCount)  # Seleccionar solo variables relevantes

# Normalizar los datos
movies_scaled <- scale(movies_cleaned)

# Mostrar un resumen del dataset limpio
summary(movies_scaled)

# 2. Prueba de Hopkins

hopkins_stat <- hopkins(movies_scaled, n = nrow(movies_scaled) * 0.1)  # Usamos el 10% de los datos
## Warning in hopkins(movies_scaled, n = nrow(movies_scaled) * 0.1): Package
## `clustertend` is deprecated.  Use package `hopkins` instead.
hopkins_stat
## $H
## [1] 0.06949508
# 3. Visual Assessment of Cluster Tendency (VAT)
if (nrow(movies_scaled) < 5000) {
  fviz_dist(dist(movies_scaled), show_labels = FALSE) +
    ggtitle("VAT - Evaluación Visual de la Tendencia al Agrupamiento")
} else {
  cat("El dataset es demasiado grande para la VAT. Se recomienda usar una muestra.")
}

# 4. Conclusiones
cat("\n--- Análisis y Conclusiones ---\n",
    "1. El estadístico de Hopkins es", round(hopkins_stat$H, 3), ".\n")
